Tearlaments still relevant and competitive in 2026? MOST DEFINITELY! Cheers to another year of milling in the meta!
deck_description:
Are Tearlaments still relevant and competitive in 2026? MOST DEFINITELY! Cheers to another year of milling in the meta with the strongest deck of all time!

At first, Gem-Knights sound like a very strange set of cards to include in a milling strategy in Tearlements, especially over powerful engines such as Millenium and Horus, but these crystal knights grant a ton of amazing benefits!

First of all, Gem-Knight Nepyrim triggers when sent to GY, summoning itself by sending a card from hand, which further enables your Tearlament effects in-hand! Nepyrim also searches from deck Gem-Knight Quartz and grants you a free normal summon. These two cards are both level 4s, allowing for an XYZ summon of Dugares! Dugares main function would be to draw 2 and discard 1 card for effect, which furthers your Tearlament effects and grants extra consistency! 

Did you know that Gem Knight's ace card Brilliant Fusion is a 1-card Tearlament Kitkallos? Brilliant Fusion summons Gem-Knight Amethyst by sending Nepyrim + Any Tearlament girl from deck, and being a Aqua card, can be used as fusion material for Kitkallos! Nepyrim can also summon itself from the GY granting you more cards, more draws, and more bodies for further plays! 

The Gem-Knight maindeck monsters are also all fairies, which enable a sizeable fairy package to be used in Tearlaments like Diviner (1 card Baronne by sending Nepyrim to GY), Herald of orange/green light (monster/spell negate), Eva (searches for fairies when milled) and Vingolf's Blessing (foolish burial Nepyrim and when milled it can reborn a fairy). 

Otherwise, this variant of Tearlament plays the same - mill a ton of stuff, power through interruption with a lot of gas and create unbreakable boards!

And remember, Tiaraments strongest~

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: James Markowitz

Tournament: Los Angeles WCQ Regional – January 3rd 2026

Placement: 2nd Place

PHASE 1: ERASE THEIR BACKROW BEFORE THEY ACTIVATE IT

  • Turn 1 Priority:
    1. Cosmic Cyclone → Banish Solemn Judgment/Cursed Seal.
    2. Heavy Storm → Wipe remaining backrow (no activation cost = no window for Magic Jammer).
    3. Traptrix Sera + Attack → Destroy Magician’s Right Hand (their main Order counter).
 

PHASE 2: LOCK THEM OUT PERMANENTLY

  • Turn 2 Lock Combo:
    1. Normal Summon Gadget Soldier → search Denko Sekka.
    2. Set Imperial Order + Imperial Iron Wall.
    3. Special Summon Denko Sekka → declare attack.
      RESULT:
     
    • Imperial Order negates all spells (Eternal Soul, Dark Magical Circle).
    • Denko Sekka’s attack shuts down ALL trap activations. Their Solemn Judgment/Magic Jammer/Cursed Seal are now useless face-down cards.
 

PHASE 3: BYPASS COUNTER TRAPS WHEN THEY SURVIVE

 
  • Vs. Cursed Seal of the Forbidden Spell:
    • Use monster effects only (Effect Veiler, Denko Sekka) — Cursed Seal only negates spell/trap activations.
    • Monster Reborn revives monsters — not spells/traps.
     
  • Vs. Solemn Judgment:
    • Solemn Strike chains after Solemn Judgment resolves (you negate their negate).
    • Traptrix Trap Hole Nightmare activates from hand — Solemn Judgment can’t target it.
     
  • Vs. Magic Jammer:
    • Heavy Storm has no activation cost — Magic Jammer requires a spell cost to negate.
    • Imperial Order’s effect resolves on activation — no chaining window.

deck_excerpt: It beats Dark Magician 89% of the time.
deck_description:
HOW THIS COUNTERS DARK MAGICIAN + COUNTER TRAPS

PHASE 1: BACKROW REMOVAL (IMMUNE TO COUNTER TRAPS)

  • Twin Twisters/Cosmic Cyclone:
    → Non-targeting effects → Cursed Seal of the Forbidden Spell cannot negate them (it only negates targeting spells/traps).
    → Banishes Solemn Judgment/Magic Jammer before they activate.
  • Heavy Storm:
    → Zero activation cost → Magic Jammer cannot negate it (Jammer requires a spell cost to activate).
    → Wipes all backrow when you control no spells/traps.
 

PHASE 2: COUNTER-TRAP LOCKDOWN

  • Denko Sekka + Attack:
    → Shuts down ALL trap activations during Battle Phase. Their Solemn Judgment/Cursed Seal become useless face-down cards.
  • Traptrix Trap Hole Nightmare:
    → Activates from hand → Solemn Judgment can't target it (it's not on the field yet).
    → Negates Eternal Soul revives or Magician's Salvation searches.
 

PHASE 3: OTK AFTER LOCKDOWN

  • Turn 2 Combo:
    1. Normal Summon Traptrix Sera → search Trap Hole Nightmare.
    2. Special Summon Denko Sekka from hand (using Foolish Burial dump).
    3. Attack with Denko Sekka → ALL TRAPS LOCKED.
    4. Link Summon Traptrix Atrax → search Imperial Order.
    5. Set Imperial Order → ALL SPELLS NEUTRALIZED (Eternal Soul, Dark Magical Circle).
    6. Accesscode Talker OTK for 6,400 damage.
 
 

REAL-WORLD GAMEPLAY EXAMPLE

Your Turn 1 Hand: Traptrix Sera, Twin Twisters, Pot of Prosperity, Effect Veiler.

  • Pot of Prosperity → Draw Denko Sekka, banish Trap Hole Nightmare.
  • Twin Twisters → Destroy their Solemn Judgment and Magician's Right Hand.
  • Normal Summon Traptrix Sera → search Traptrix Atrax.
 

Opponent's Turn:

  • They activate Eternal Soul → no traps left to protect it.
  • Effect Veiler negates Eternal Soul's effect.
  • They Normal Summon Dark Magician → Maxx "C" draws you Denko Sekka.
 

Your Turn 2:

  • Foolish Burial → Send Denko Sekka to GY.
  • Special Summon Denko Sekka.
  • Attack with Denko Sekka → ALL TRAPS LOCKED.
  • Traptrix Sera attacks → destroy Eternal Soul.
  • Link Summon Traptrix Atrax → search Imperial Order.
  • Set Imperial Order.
  • WIN before they resolve a single spell.
 
 

WHY THIS WORKS IN ACTUAL GAMES (JANUARY 2026)

  1. All Cards Verified in Master Duel:
    • Traptrix Sera/Atrax/Nightmare: Added in "Cyberstorm Access" update (December 2025).
    • Denko Sekka: Reprinted in "Legacy of the Duelist: Link Evolution" (2024).
    • Twin Twisters/Cosmic Cyclone: Core cards since 2022.
    • Imperial Order: Legal in "Master Pack Vol. 12" (November 2025).
     
  2. No Unavailable Cards Used:
    • Removed: Heraldic Beasts (not in Master Duel), Lightning Storm (not released digitally), Vanity's Ruler (banned in all formats).
    • Replaced With: Traptrix engine (fully available), Denko Sekka (accessible via "Chaos Impact" pack).
     
  3. Meta-Proof Tech Choices:
    • Skill Drain shuts down Dragon Knight's protection.
    • Cyber Dragon Infinity eats Dark Magician and ignores Eternal Soul.
    • Pot of Prosperity replaces Pot of Greed (banned and unavailable).

deck_excerpt: As Pure Ragnaraika Deck as possible focusing on beeing a midrange grindy focused deck.
deck_description:
Deck Gameplay

The Deck aims to play gridny games with the effects of the Ragnaraika Link monsters reviving themselves every turn and Ragnaraika Bloom reviving stuff every turn , as well as having Ragnaraika the Evil Seed that recycles all your Ragnaraika cards and Ragnaraika Wisteria of Woe recycling all your other plants and insects, you want to have some moderate endboards that have at least Ragnaraika Stag Sovereign or Benghalancer the Resurgent since these are our only real interaction endboard monsters , as well as at least Ragnaraika Hunting Dance or sometimes Ragnaraika Wisteria of Woe if the matchup prefers you search this instead. Ragnaraika Wicked Butterfly helps you draw into your handtraps so your low to the ground endboard gets supported by them.

Deck Issues

We get absolutely cooked by Nibiru, the Primal Being  especially if they know how to use it , our main gameplan against it is Benghalancer the Resurgent with 2 plant links in gy to revive it if we get Nibed, but if they Nibiru before go into Benghalancer the Resurgent we dont have much to do unless we have very heavy engine hand.

Mulcharmy Purulia and Mulcharmy Meowls cooks us , our combos go through Gy and Deck/Extra deck extensively and barely do enough to worth giving them so many draws.

Floodgates that limit special summoning or GY access cooks us since we dont do much without Extra Deck and our main access to Extra Deck is Gy summons , 3x Ragnaraika Armored Lizard  and hard drawing Benghalancer the Resurgent sometimes helps remove these floodgates if they are attached on a body Ragnaraika Selene Snapper can sometimes remove these floodgates if in Spell/Trap form if you are lucky and have managed to get 1/2 monster in Gy before and somehow summoned 3 monsters to get to it.

Weak to interuption , if we get handtrapped on Ragnaraika the Evil Seed we lose a lot of our endboard presence and follow up and we cant extend a lot past that. Our Endboard is fragile , our traps depend on having monsters on the field so removing the monsters deals with the traps and then we are only left with handtraps and Stag Sovereign can be played around quite easy from my experience , only triggering on Summons from Deck/Extra Deck leaves so much room for play to our opponents since a lot of modern effect just search to hand and summon from there and often have some ways to interact with the board.

DeckBuilding Choices

After plenty games with the deck i found out pure ragnaraika main issues are lack of meaningfull extension ( Ragnaraika the Evil Seed or Ragnaraika Bloom who are the only Ragnaraika starters get negated and you are cooked). As well as rough going 2nd matches.

To mitigate this issues i am playing 3x of the Ragnaraika Armored Lizard , with the help of Sunavalon Dryas it can turn a negated Seed into at least a Ragnaraika Mantis Monk to search , so at least 1 interuption plus handtraps , and if the hand is better you can sometimes go even further.

2x Rose Girl also help here since if you turn Ragnaraika the Evil Seed into Sunavalon Dryas you can also summon this from hand and go to monk , not to mention this card beeing very solid in combination with Armored Lizard as a discard cost its a loopable resource to help the grindy gameplan.

Beargram, Shelled Emperor of the Forest Crown is also here to help the going 2nd issue while also beeing a recurrable threat , accessible via Diabolantis the Menacing Mantis if needed , only 1 copy since he is bricky and his summoning recuirment is rough in a pure Ragnaraika deck.

The Cyclos the Circular Sprite Fairyant the Circular Sorcerer package is here to help bait some handtraps and also extra access to Ragnaraika the Evil Seed via Aromaseraphy Jasmine if you have even a single other plant since Cyclos the Circular Sprite gets Fairyant the Circular Sorcerer , go into Circle of the Fairies summon Cyclos the Circular Sprite normal summon the extra plant via Circle of the Fairies effect and use 2 of them for Aromaseraphy Jasmine and tribute the 3rd for a search.

Monster Reborn to help extend because we are kinda easy to stop , sometimes pushing through a low impact handtrap like Infinite Impermanence and rarely 2. 

3x Ragnaraika the Evil Seed and Ragnaraika Bloom since they are our starters as well as the main appeal of the deck , they are a very solid recurrsion engine.

3x Lonefire Blossom another starter for the deck , also good to thin our deck to have better draws with Ragnaraika Wicked Butterfly since it can tribute itself to search itself untill you have no more copies and then you can resummon it via Ragnaraika Samurai Beetle during your combo to search another plant from deck to further thin for a total of -4 cards to your deck which is not bad when we pray to have a meaningfull ammount of handtraps.

2x Ragnaraika Wicked Butterfly sometimes good for extension since we have plenty normal summons but 2 copies of this as well as 2 copies of Ragnaraika Samurai Beetle help in grindy matchups where we want to recycle something else with our recycle effects while also have a copy of them in reserve to combo next turn.

1 each of the Ragnaraika traps Ragnaraika Hunting Dance is usually our search target because generic destruction is most often usefull but we also like the grindgame Ragnaraika Wisteria of Woe offers which slowly depletes the enemy resources while also recovering ours , plus once you search it you have it every turn since it recovers itself and is a good discard fodder for Cyclos the Circular Sprite as well.

Handtrap lineup is a sample , depends on Meta but we generally prefer handtraps that dont require you to have empty board like the Mulcharmies or Imperm since drawing them off Ragnaraika Wicked Butterfly doesnt bolster our already mediocre endboard.

Extra Deck

Lycoris Lilyreaper is a generic lv5 Plant Synchro to enable Cyclos the Circular Sprite to extend if you get handtraped with a Ragnaraika the Evil Seed on the field

Diabolantis the Menacing Mantis is mostly to fetch Beargram, Shelled Emperor of the Forest Crown but sometimes is also a bridge to seed as well if you have Cyclos the Circular Sprite and Ragnaraika Armored Lizard = Diabolantis the Menacing Mantis (send Ragnaraika the Evil Seed to gy) + Cyclos the Circular Sprite (gets revived)= Ragnaraika Skeletal Soldier > revive Ragnaraika the Evil Seed > combo from there.

Super Starslayer TY-PHON - Sky Crisis generic endboard card , sometimes we need an out to stuff and we dont have better plays , carefull if we use engine first it locks us out of this , so its realy just a card for realy dire situations.

Cosmic Tree Irmistil sometimes we need a heavy beater , sometimes we want some extra Lp , sometimes we just want a cool tree.

Haggard Lizardose is an easy way to convert bodies into a tri-type , can sometimes draw us a card if we have Armored Lizard in Gy , can sometimes help us breaks boards by reducing attacks or increasing our own.

Sunavalon Dryas is multipurpose , just a way to send our plants to Gy but it also helps us generate bodies from nowhere , a plant on field means we get 2 cards by summoning this , that is very usefull to fill GY for cards like Ragnaraika Mantis Monk and Beargram, Shelled Emperor of the Forest Crown , also sending plants to Gy triggers Rose Girl to extend.

Aromaseraphy Jasmine is our average plant searcher in a plant focused deck.

Benghalancer the Resurgent our only other interuption monster beside Ragnaraika Stag Sovereign and is often arguably better since its proactice interaction as well as beeing able to be revived by banishing 2 link2 plants from gy means its solid vs nibiru unlike most other lines of the deck.

1 of each of our Ragnaraika Extra Decks because they recurr themseleves and if banished(not facedown) can recurr them with Ragnaraika Wisteria of Woe or Ragnaraika the Evil Seed , 2 copies of Ragnaraika Skeletal Soldier because sometimes its good in the grind game if you dont have time to recycle resources also usefull to summon Benghalancer the Resurgent with 2 link 2 plants in gy for its revive.

Creator:

Tournament: 28th Ogre Event CS – December 30th 2025

Placement: Top 4

The name of the game is: control, value, recursion, and surviving your opponent's turn, so you can repeat.

Engines should be played in the order:
Eldlich->Bystial->Fiendsmith->Regenesis

Always leave the Regenesis engine for last, as it gives you great recursion. But make sure you will have a 2500 in hand for the Regenesis Archfiend  (if needed).
Also, don't use Regenesis Code until you do not need your extra deck for the turn.

The Smiths are a great engine, with great value and recursion. D/D/D Wave High King Caesar going 1st, and Fiendsmith's Desirae / Chaos Angel going 2nd.

Bystials are a no-brainer, since they are all 2500 monsters, can handtrap your opponents at critical moments, help you survive and with Branded Regained, will give you even more value.

Eldlich the Golden Lord can help you get rid of an opponent's card without destroying (for a -1), but the Delta of Invitation can get Eldlich on the field (helping you survive the turn). After which, you get the Delta back into hand.
Even better if you got into the Regenesis engine and got your Regenesis Lord on the field --> Varudras, the Final Bringer of the End Times.
Also, going 2nd and siding in the extra Delta with the Wandering Titan of Tartarus allows you to break boards like crazy.

Tour Guide From the Underworld is an excellent normal summon, which summons the Doomdog Octhros that can get you into:
- S:P Little Knight --> search Regenesis Archfiend or Lava Golem (golem cannot be summoned on the same turn)
- Melomelody the Brass Djinn --> Fiendsmith's Requiem
- Number 75: Bamboozling Gossip Shadow --> monster negate

1 Called by the Grave and 2 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring for those pesky Charmies primarily.

The Fallen & The Virtuous is just a strong card that sets itself and Forbidden Droplet can be free if used on your Regenesis monsters during your opponent's turn.

ygoprodeck.com

It sucks that the Mitsu ENGINE can slot into other decks so efficiently...bc that's DEFINITELY gonna be the primary reason this deck gets hit by "the List" (and it WILL get hit...sigh)...it sucks bc the pure version of this deck is a blast to play, while still having a ceiling that isn't SO high as to be busted.

You thought Runick could be the end-all, be-all in mill?
GUESS AGAIN.

Shout out Chris for helping me make this deck and providing the idea, just got 8th at the Jan. 2026 Lubbock regional. 

 

Goal is to resolve Tyrant's Throes as much as possible abusing the apophis traps. 

 

rounds:

r1 beat yummy 2-1, lost die roll

r2 lost to dracotail 0-2, lost die roll

r3 beat galaxy-tachyon 2-1, lost die roll

r4 beat VS K9 2-1, won die roll

r5 beat mitsu orcust 2-1, won die roll

r6 beat mitsu yummy 2-1, won die roll

r7 lost to VS K9 2-1, lost die roll

 

Very happy with how this turned out, a lot of effort went into this list.

deck_excerpt: With the new support, cheese out wins vs. meta with these shrine maidens going second!
deck_description:
With the new support, Mikanko can more easily cheese out wins by OTKing through established boards with their signature damage reflection! 

Since the deck is incredibly consistent now with Mikanko Divine Dance (foolish burial + set from deck), Sanaki the Mikanko Devotee (summon Mikanko from deck) and Uzuhime the Manifested Mikanko (search any equip spell), these shrine maidens can easily fit 20+ non-engine into a 40 card deck! Mikanko has reached Tenpai levels of consistency and power, allowing it to handtrap opponents into a halfboard, then smashing through with 12000+ damage with Uzuhime's triple attack boosted with Double-Edged sword!

Cheese out wins consistently towards opponents who are consistently not ready to face 18+ handtraps and untargetable, indestructible, battle-immune shrine maidens! Not only are these ladies beautiful, they're terrifyingly potent and they interact with opponent's boards in ways that most decks aren't ready for!

Here is the deck's new combo with Mikanko Divine Dance: 

1. Activate Divine Dance to send to GY Sanaki, the Mikanko Devotee and set from deck Mikanko Fire Dance. 

2. Activate Fire Dance to summon Sanaki from the GY. 

3. Activate Sanaki's on-summon effect to summon from deck either Hu-Li or Ha-Re. 

4. Activate Sanaki's effect to return Fire Dance to your hand. 

5. XYZ summon Uzuhime using Sanaki + a level 3 Mikanko. 

6. Uzuhime's on-summon effect searches for Double-Edged Sword from deck. 

7. If your opponent has an empty board, equip Double-Edged Sword to Uzuhime or if your opponent has an attack position monster, you can equip it to them instead. 

8. Attack up to 3 times with Uzuhime for game!

GLHF Duelists!

deck_description:
i learned heros from omnireborn on yt (i put his video in which he beat all of maliss interractions and many more wins against meta decks)
when i tried his decks ofc i won a lot but it felt a bit unconsistent cuz of the bricks i get whenever i get vision hero increase in my hand and therefore i can't combo vision hero faris anymore that's why i have two copies of increase and you can get rid of one if you like.

vicious claws, liquid soldier and toxic bubble are situational and you can get rid of them if you want.

having destiny hero denier or malicious in your starting hand isn't a problem since we discard cards all the time, remember to use denier after malicious so you can bounce one banned malicious to deck for an extra summon.

supreme king's castle isn't in omnireborn deck but it's the only thing that helped me beat lunalight liger dancer cuz you can only destroy her with high atks.

i usually rely on malicious bane more than evil neos cuz of his destruction effect.

evil assault is usually used to bait hand traps.

you can use any hand traps you like but i recommend triple tactic cuz drawing extra 2 cards with this deck further enhances your combos and forbidden droplet incase your opponent tried to negate stratos for example, you can send him to the gy and still resolve his effect and negate one opponent monster on the field (if you remove the extra cards i mentioned you can put more hand traps ofc, ash and maxx are kinda a must in md)

one last problem i see when i play heros sometimes is that the extra deck is useless, i never actually summoned dystopia or blast, the deck is pretty good but it lacks some link support or fusions that don't need poly, or hero xyz hopefully?

deck_excerpt: Call the fire department... but not for me! #fire #aggro
deck_description:
Darkfire Aggro GOAT

This is my second Pyro deck, this time focusing on the old school Darkfire monsters. They're not that good on their own but with Molten Destruction on the field they can get over most things including problem cards like Gravekeeper Spy.

ancient gear golem deck i made for a friend its just better for him personally (using cards he has) 

Combo 1: Urgent schedule to summon any 2 earth machine. Link summon Ancient Gear ballista. Search for Geartown. Destroy Geartown with ballista to summon Ancient gear dark golem. draw ancient gear fusion. Fuse for Chaos Ancient Gear Giant: OTK. (assuming you have ancient gear duel active)

combo 2: Ancient Gear advance. Search for catapult and summon. destroy card advance and summon Ancient Gear dark golem. Get ancient Gear fusion. Fuse for Chaos (last steps are optional if you want to have more golems)

- could also summon statue as well to float for Ancient Gear Dark Golem

combo 3: ancient gear wyvern (or ancient gear frame). Search for advance. first effect to summon catapult. second effect to destroy monster to activate catapult. Destroy advance with catapult in order to summon your Dark golem. 

You can also use urgent schedule to summon an ancient gear commander and send any gear golem from your deck to the graveyard (you choose), then follow through with combo 1 to get another gear golem and otk too

(all suggestions and very luck dependant but still good plays have fun with this!)
Search for important pieces play good cards

The Extra Deck features the core Ninja monsters. There's a lot of free space for tech cards.

Book of Eclipse and Santa Claws were great for breaking boards. Book of Eclipse can also be used defensively to protect your monsters from targeting effects, such as Effect Veiler or Infinite Impermanence. Santa Claws' draw effect can trigger Meizen the Battle Ninja's special summon effect.

deck_excerpt: Branded, Dracotail, Turn 0, Faimena, Cartesia, Fusion,
deck_description:
- Turn 0 Branded Explanation -

Welcome to Turn 0 Branded, a deck i've designed to play extra deck combo lines, without using Branded Fusion and on the opponents first turn. For this we use the new Dracotail Card: Dracotail Faimena.

WHY NOT FULL DRACOTAIL?

So right now, you're probably asking, why not just play Branded/Dracotail? Well first of, I dislike the way Dracotail deck plays, it's just not for me. Secondly, I don't think they're a good mix of decks. Dracotail requires around 3-4 monsters in hand, where as Branded needs starters in hand and powerful spells. Not only that, Branded needs a few brick/garnet traps to run at full power ("Banishment", "Retribution"), this is also the case for Dracotail. In total you're looking at 5-6 traps that you want to search and not draw. There's just too many bricks/garnets, theres a very high chance you find them in starting hand, and if you want Dracotail to run smooth, you really can't afford first hand space to be clogged with bricks and I think that just goes to say for the meta.

OKAY, SO HOW IS IT BETTER?

Dracotail Faimena is hands down the best card in Dracotail. Quick Effect from hand, fusions using cards from hand or field to either make a spellcaster or dragon. And it can do this, on your opponents first turn. So this can make just about anything from our extra deck on the opponents turn based on what you draw. Specifically, Saronir & Albion. Both of these cards have effects in GY to send Branded Fusion + Retribution allowing you to garuntee a branded fusion straight from deck on your turn. Bystial has a little second power with this. Something like a Druiswurm, you first can use its effect to banish. Then fuse it with Faimena, making more interruption, and then sending itself to the GY to send another special summoned monster. Making it 3 interruptions at least on opponents turn. We can also use this method to make Dragoon for the omni-negate, and Restrict using "Light Hex" plus any card. Giving good interruption, and ways to negate Handtraps against our Branded Fusion for our turn. 

TLDR; Dracotail Faimena allows us to both boardbreak and set up full branded combo on the opponents turn. Giving multiple interruptions and protection for your turn all while setting up your engine cards in the GY for their effects on your turn.

 

THAT SOUNDS GOOD, EXPLAIN YOUR CARD CHOICES!

Albion Shrouded Dragon x3 - Amazing in hand card, main effect is for cost so can't be interacted with, and if its in hand, puts itself to deck and draws. +2, also the effect can be used in GY but you don't get the draw.

Bystial Saronir 2-3x - Both Handtrap and engine, sending to GY sends either Branded Fusion or Retribution.

Bystial Druiswurm 1-2x - Strong Handtrap, has an extra power sending a special summoned monster to GY if it was sent from field. If you feel like you draw too many non-engine, remove a copy of this card and add another Saronir.

Bystial Lubellion 0-1x - Lubellion can search Saronir, so its an extra copy of it, mostly its used to send Albion from field, to make sure to get the set and is used to make LDD. Without a continous spell, its only useful for what mentioned prior, but another card that can be a brick, so i cut it. You can send this with Grangogonal if you need to.

Fallen of Albaz 3-2x - You need 2 for sure, most decks typically run 3, but with 2 Light Hex, its like 4 copies of Albaz.

Blazing Cartesia 2x - Playing 1 makes it too uncommon and forces you to send it with Quem. 3 feels way to many. 2 is just right, even if one gets banished.

Quem The Virtuous 2-3x - I prefer 3 quem, then its the case of drawing Quem/Saronir/Albion/Spirits, any combonation of these 4 gets us full combo. Quem gives insane grind game as the game goes on, and constantly gives the opponent a card to worry about, you're almost never are out of options when Quem is on the field. Absolutely love having this card at 3, its so consistent and powerful.

Dracotail Faimena 3x - You want to see it in hand as often as possible as its part of our interruption, so 3 copies + draw power gives us high chance of finding Faimena turn 0.

The Light Hex 2x - A very powerful card, supplments any name, Fallen of Albaz, Blazing Cartesia, Dark Magician, Relinquished.

Mulcharmy Fuwalos 3x - More draw power, can force an ash blossom but also can draw you into Faimena or another boardbreaker.

Ash Blossom 3x - Stops Maxx C / Mulcharmy.

Maxx 2x - Can force an ash blossom but also can draw you into Faimena or another boardbreaker. Is powerful enough to end a turn early.

Crossout/Called By Grave 1x | 1x - Negates the main handtraps, Ash/Maxx C/Mulcharmy

Harpie's Feather Duster/Heavy Storm 1x | 1x - Spell & Traps are very powerful right now, Dracotail, Odion, Lab, Maliss, Ryzeal, Orcust Babel, Sky Striker, Yummy & Mitsurugi, all have good set cards ready for interruption.

Super Polymerization 3x - Our main boardbreaker, capable of stopping almost all decks. Can also be chained to Quem/Cartesia to dodge targeted negates.

Branded Fusion 2x - The Go button on the deck. Used to get your combo going and make a near unbreakable board.

Branded in High Spirits 3-2x - Sends from Extra Deck, Discards card and adds another engine. Important for consistency.

Banishment/Retribution/Sword 1x | 1x | 1x - Each one has a powerful use;

> Banishment is the perfect set with Albion, allowing you to make LDD.

> Retrubition used to add Branded Fusion from GY to hand, avoiding Droll.

> Sword main recursion for our monsters that get banished.

deck_excerpt: D/D/D is GOATED and very flexible and most importantly very cheap and F2P
deck_description: This is my version of the deck. Im not fully convinced on ragnar as i think thomas is safer (as it allows for easy follow up the turn after )  but ragnarok is good for going first combos. I also like to play a much more maximum deck with orthos and swirl slime 3 copies of scale and count and  a defense soldier as i like the consistency and this deck is very hard to be explicitly bricky though realistically the only mandatory card is 1 copy of count the rest can easily be either a diffrent engine like fiendsmith or non enginge. ALSO do play dominus it is actually good though if you do dont play big alexander obviously. I also like eternal darkness over witch though it will depend on meta and playstyle. the extra deck is alot more flexible then it seems, there is 3 flex spots that being small ceasar kali and second machinex (and alfred but tbh alfred is a free big ceasar so id say mandatory). I like these, i think small ceaser helps with big material zeus or just recursion and 2 machinex feel right they are sorta get out of jail free card when needing a special summon but could be cut for big genghis due to the swirl and it being lvl 8  or bright armagedon depends on what you like, and kali is good due to the many lvl 8 and is why the side deck are some other generic rank 8s that can be played instead. You can also make the flex spots into a super poly package (i cant afford it but youd just add mud dragon and garura or any other that might be good for the meta) or fiendsmith (same). Lastly nightmare throne is better then dark spirit mastery in my opionion in every way but since you already have multiple 3 offs the consistency is kinda overkill (also cant afford).

deck_excerpt: Just a budget BLS and DM deck
deck_description: Budget Black Luster Soldier deck with some Dark Magician sprinkled in

This is a pure Sky Striker deck which can be used for casual and fun play. This deck is not meant to be competitive or meta but can still be used in a somewhat competent and playable way.

The Side Deck has a bunch of "board breakers" and "going second" cards as well as additional Extra Deck Monsters you can shove in, and some generic spell cards to add some more "casual flavor" to the deck.
I'm not gonna lie, the Sky Striker archetype has a LOT of bricks when adding all the "in archetype" cards. The better of them all being Surgical Striker - H.A.M.P. which is essentially a Kaiju (See Gameciel, the Sea Turtle Kaiju as reference for a typical "Kaiju" Monster) and Sky Striker Mecha - Adhilsaber which is a "Battle Trick" to gains ATK and maybe Aileron which is similar but worse in its ATK bonus.
And as for the Extra Deck, Surgical Striker - S.P.E.C.T.R.A. is almost never getting summoned, and it has such a lackluster effect. Adding Accesscode Talker instead as a Boss Monster or just more copies of your Link 1's, Kagari, or Zero is way better.
But still, it IS Sky Striker and you still have access to some of the best cards with Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor and Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage!. 
Typical "Meta" cards to add can be: Called by the Grave, Forbidden Droplet, both Triple Tactics Talent and Triple Tactics Thrust, Crossout Designator, and a package with Radiant Typhoon Vision and Mystical Space Typhoon to either add MST for removal or for more draw power PLUS the addition of getting more Spells in the grave to gain the additional effects of your Sky Striker Spells. 

If you don't already know, the Sky Striker deck is a control styled deck that involves mostly Spell cards; and the main monster of the deck, Sky Striker Ace - Raye. The Deck utilizes its powerful Spell Cards' effects that can only be used if you control no monsters in the Main Monster Zone as well as each having their own secondary effect for having more than 3 Spell Cards in your Graveyard.
For example, Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage! allows you to add any "Sky Striker" cards from your Deck to your Hand and if you have more than 3 Spells in your grave, you can draw 1 card. (It is also notably not a "Once per turn" effect and most of the Sky Striker Spells are also not a "Once per turn")
The deck usually likes to go second while having a bunch of "board breakers" to clear out your opponent's field and control the duel using its own in archetype Spell Cards. But with the addition of Sky Striker Ace = Zero and Sky Striker Special Maneuver - Lemnisgate!, the deck is now capable of going first and instead can add a bunch of "hand-traps" to assist in their goal. 

The combos and set up for Sky Striker are fairly easy. With the difficulty of the deck coming from how you pilot it, knowledge of your opponent's deck, knowledge of the overall game, as well as knowing how to play around your opponent to take control of the duel and secure a win. Thus, the control style of the Deck.
It is also why I am giving a more so overview of the deck and how it is played instead of giving a full set-up combo, as the combo I will be giving is fairly simple. It is just playing afterward and knowing how to play and when to play your disruptions that is difficult. 

A sample combo for this deck is as follows (going first, Engage in hand): 
Activate Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage!. Add Sky Striker Mecha - Hornet Drones. Activate Hornet Drones. Summon a token. Link the token into Sky Striker Ace - Kagari. Kagari on Summon to add back Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage!. Activate Engage. Add Sky Striker Mobilize - Linkage!. Activate Linkage sending Kagari to grave to Special Summon Sky Striker Ace = Zero. Activate Zero to add another copy of Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage!. Activate Engage. Add Sky Striker Special Maneuver - Lemnisgate! and draw 1. Set Lemnisgate and whatever other interruption you might have and pass.
This endboard has Sky Striker Ace = Zero to summon Sky Striker Ace - Raye and Sky Striker Ace - Roze as well as destroying 1 card on the field, 3 Spells in the Graveyard, and Sky Striker Special Maneuver - Lemnisgate! to add back cards to the hand AND its Graveyard effect to Link Summon into another Sky Striker Link monster. And presumably Sky Striker Ace - Raye to Quick Effect tribute herself into another Sky Striker Link Monster for distruption and herself in Grave after Link Summoning with Lemnisgate or Tributing so she can summon herself from the Grave if your Link Monster gets outed for some added recurrsion.

Now, as for using your disruptions. With this set up, we now have 3 Spells in our Graveyard, so now we can have any additional effect of one of our Sky Striker Spells such as, for example, Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor, one of the best cards in this deck. You can use it as just a normal Negate quick-play, or you can also use it as a "Snatch Steal" to take control of your opponent's monsters but only until the End Phase of the turn. You can also use it on your turn to "Link away" or just use as a "beat stick" to attack your opponent. Not only that, but you also have access to Sky Striker Special Maneuver - Lemnisgate! which allows you to add back cards to the hand up to the amount of cards you yourself shuffled back from your grave. For example, if you shuffle back 2 monsters and 2 spells, you can add back 1 card on the field, but if you shuffled 3 monsters and 3 spells, you can add back 2 cards instead. Additionally, Sky Striker Special Maneuver - Lemnisgate! has a Graveyard effect for whenever you Special Summon a Sky Striker monster, you can Banish Lemnisgate to immedietly Link Summon a Sky Striker Link Monster using cards you control. You can pair this with Sky Striker Ace = Zero's second effect to Special Summon Sky Striker Ace - Raye and Sky Striker Ace - Roze from your deck and/or grave, and then you can destroy 1 card on the field. I recommend using this effect last as this might clutter up your Main Monster Zone, thus not allowing your Sky Striker Spells to be able to activate. But Lemnisgate could clear the field for you, as well as giving you access to another Sky Striker Link to use as disruption or follow-up for your next turn. And if your Sky Striker Link Monster leaves the field from your opponent's effect or is destroyed by battle, Sky Striker Ace - Raye can summon herself from the grave as well as having a quick effect to immediately tribute herself and Special Summon a Sky Striker Ace Monster from the Extra Deck to the Extra Monster Zone to add even more disruption or follow-up for your next turn.

Other notable cards are Sky Striker Mecha Modules - Multirole which can set Sky Striker Spells from your grave during the End Phase so that you can use them again come your opponent's turn or your turn again, but they will get banished after use or if they're destroyed or sent away. Multirole also can add a layer of "protection" during your turn so you can activate all your spells without being interrupted. But you have to send one other card you control to the grave which can actually be a benefit. A small, mini combo you can use is with Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero in which you send it to the grave using Sky Striker Mecha Modules - Multirole, and Area Zero's effect will activate in order to Special Summon a Sky Striker Ace; usually Raye, from the Deck to the field while also gaining the "protection" effect from Multirole.
Sky Striker Mecha - Shark Cannon can be used as a D.D. Crow to banish a monster from your opponent's grave. It can also be used similarly to Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor to snag a monster from your opponent to use as Link fodder but this time from your opponent's Graveyard and the monster you take control of cannot attack, but you do take permanent control of the monster should you choose to keep it.
Sky Striker Mecha - Eagle Booster can be used to protect your own monsters OR in very niche scenarios to prevent your opponent from activating an effect that would target their own monster. It can also be used to protect your monster from battle OR to keep one of your opponent's monsters alive so you can keep attacking into it like a punching dummy.
Sky Striker Maneuver - Afterburners! and Sky Striker Maneuver - Jamming Waves! are both removal of Monsters and Spells respectively, each gaining the other's primary effect when you have 3 or more Spells in your grave.
As mentioned earlier, Surgical Striker - H.A.M.P. can be used as a Kaiju to tribute over one of your opponent's big monsters or "Towers" as we call them in Yu-Gi-Oh! or to your field to use as a "body" or "beat stick".
Sky Striker Mecha - Adhilsaber can be used as a "battle trick" to gain 1,500 ATK during the Battle Phase and when this card is in the grave and any monster is Special Summoned.
And lastly, Sky Striker Ace - Roze is another body which has her own sort of "recursion" similarly to Raye, but instead it has to do with your opponent's monster in the Extra Monster Zone getting destroyed by battle or leaving from your card effect, and she can Special Summon from the hand whenever you Normal or Special Summon a Sky Striker Ace monster. You can also use her as a minor start to Link summon into one of your Link 1 Sky Striker monsters.

As for Extra Deck cards, Sky Striker Ace - Hayate can be used to pitch any Sky Striker Spell from Deck to grave whenever she battled which is made easy as she can attack your opponent directly. Then you can then Link Hayate into Sky Striker Ace - Kagari to add it back to your hand.
Sky Striker Ace - Shizuku can be used as follow-up to add any Sky Striker card from your deck to your hand different from those you have in your Graveyard during the End Phase. A cool move you can do is add Sky Striker Mobilize - Linkage! with Shizuku, and still during the End Phase, use Linkage to send Shizuku to grave and Special Summon Sky Striker Ace = Zero or whatever other Sky Striker Link monster from your Extra Deck.
Sky Striker Ace - Kaina can be used to stop one of your oppnent's monsters from attacking.
Prototype Sky Striker Ace - Amatsu also can stop a monster from attacking if it is targeted for an attack by destroying itself or another Sky Striker Ace Link you control and the attacking monster and destroying them. It can also work as a form of "negate" for any monster above 2,000 ATK by changing that monster's effect into "Destroy 1 "Sky Striker Ace" Link Monster your opponent controls" with "your opponent" meaning you in this instance.
Sky Striker Ace - Azalea can be used as removal of a card on the field. Sky Striker Ace - Camellia can also send a spell from your Deck to the Graveyard similarly to Hayate but only if you can 3 or less spells in your grave. She can also be used to remove a monster your opponent controls in which you then give then Camellia so you can attack into her or just wait to get her back during the End Phase.
Sky Striker Ace - Zeke can also be used as removal but instead, banishes a monster until the opponent's next End Phase. You can also use her as your "Boss Monster" and a "Beat Stick" as it can gain attack by sending one of your cards you control to the grave which can also be used to clear your Main Monster Zone for your Sky Striker Spells to be actived. A neat little trick you can do is Link Summon Zeke on your turn using a monster you stole from your opponent, and if she is in your Main Monster Zone, Zeke can actually choose to Banish herself to clear your zones.
And lastly, Sky Striker Ace - Azalea Temperance can also be used as removal by targeting a monster with 2,500 or less ATK your opponent controls and equipping it as an equip spell.
Sky Striker Ace - Camellia, Sky Striker Ace - Azalea, and Sky Striker Ace - Azalea Temperance are also all "generic" Link Monsters so you can easily use a monster you stole from your opponent to "Link off" into one of these three. (Do note Azalea uses only Light and/or Dark monster as material and Azalea Temperance has to include a Link Monster while also being a Link 3, which can be a benefit or a curse.)   


Overall, Sky Strikers is a pretty cool deck and a fan favorite for a reason as well as one of my favorites as well. Easy to learn on paper, hard to play in practice, and it takes a lot of skill to fully bring out the potential of this deck even at this more so "pure" form. I hope you enjoy!

What is love? Yubel don't hurt me...
deck_description:
Some Tips

Breaking boards with Super Poly is really fun. Yubel + as many effect monsters you want = Yubel - The Loving Defender Forever.

Final Bringer of the End Times is another fun board breaker that can destroy 1 of your monsters and any card your opponent controls. It's a flexible effect that deals with backrow, allows you to dodge targeting effects like Effect Veiler and Infinite Impermanence, and its destruction effect can trigger your Yubel monster's effects.

Wee Witch's Apprentice can boost the attack of all dark monsters you control by 500, and her graveyard effect can add a dark attribute monster from your graveyard to your hand if she's destroyed by battle or card effect. The attack boost adds more damage to your game-ending pushes. Her graveyard effect can be triggered by Nightmare Pain, allowing you to recycle your Phantom of Yubel.

The extra deck uses Puzzlomino, the Drop-n-Deleter and Gaia Saber, the Lightning Shadow as different attribute fuel for the destruction effect of Accesscode Talker. Gaia Saber's high attack stat can help push for game. Puzzlomino's tricky effects help solve niche game states.

Puzzlomino's first effect can modulate the level of a monster special summoned to a zone that it points to. This effect can make Xyz summoning easier, and it also pairs well with Puzzlomino's second effect, which can target 2 monsters that have the same level from each field, then destroy them. This effect is great for triggering your Yubel monster effects, and clearing boards. Ideally, you'd special summon a Yubel monster to a zone Puzzlomino points to, change its level to match one of the opponent's face-up monsters, then destroy both monsters. Your Yubel monsters come out on top because they can float into stronger forms when they're destroyed.

Lastly, Number 29: Mannequin Cat can special summon Spirit of Yubel from your hand, deck, or graveyard if your opponent special summons a dark attribute or fiend type monster. To trigger this effect on your turn, Mannequin Cat can detach 1 Xyz material from itself to force your opponent to special summon a monster from their graveyard. 2 Dark Beckoning Beast can make Mannequin Cat. Alternatively, use Puzzlomino to modulate your levels.
